==Standard dialogue==
* '''Mernik:''' Oh, hello! Children, say hello to the surface-dweller.
* {{trandom}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 1}}
** '''Cave goblin child:''' Haha! You look funny!
** '''Mernik:''' I'm sure you look just as funny to the surface-dweller!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 2}}
** '''Cave goblin child:''' You smell!
** '''Mernik:''' There's no need to be rude!
** '''Mernik:''' I'm sorry about that, surface-dweller.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 3}}
** '''Cave goblin child:''' Are you really from the surface?
** '''Player:''' Yes I am.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|cond=After Another Slice of H.A.M.|Dialogue 4}}
** '''Cave goblin child:''' Are you [player name]? Did you help Zanik save the city?
** '''Mernik:''' Just because [he's/she's] a surface-dweller, doesn't mean [he's/she's] [player name]! There are lots of surface-dwellers!
** '''Player:''' Actually I am [player name].
** '''Mernik:''' [Player name]? Really?
** '''Mernik:''' Zanik told me about you! I'm so pleased to meet you!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 5}}
** '''Cave goblin child:''' Shan't!
** '''Mernik:''' Well don't blame me if he doesn't want to talk to you either!
** '''Mernik:''' Sorry about that.
** {{tact|end}}
